00:00:00.200 --> 00:00:08.200
Hello everyone. Welcome to CAYIN Technology SMP-NEO series media player  tutorial video

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:20.000
This video will walk you through how to use SMP player with its embedded software SMP-NEO, to login the user interface and be ready for setup. 

00:00:24.200 --> 00:00:31.100
After you receive the package of CAYIN media player, please firstly unpack the package.

00:00:31.100 --> 00:00:36.200
Then take the following 4 Steps to complete the hardware installation

00:00:37.200 --> 00:00:43.000
You will find a media player, a power adapter, a power cord in the package. 

00:00:43.000 --> 00:00:52.100
You will also need to prepare an Ethernet cable, a USB keyboard and a mouse,
and a display with its cable.

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:58.400
Now let’s take SMP-6000 as an example and start to install this player. 

00:00:59.700 --> 00:01:00.480
STEP 1

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:10.560
Plug the Ethernet cable into the media player’s LAN port. By default, SMP player will get an IP address from a DHCP server.

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:12.460
STEP 2

00:01:12.460 --> 00:01:22.600
Connect the VGA, DVI or HDMI cable to your display. The default resolution will be your screen’s native resolution.

00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:24.640
STEP 3

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:29.400
Connect the keyboard and the mouse to any of the USB connectors.

00:01:30.380 --> 00:01:31.240
STEP 4

00:01:31.360 --> 00:01:37.900
Connect the power adapter to a socket.
SMP player will be turned on automatically by itself.

00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:42.500
The mentioned steps above can be applied to all SMP players.

00:01:42.500 --> 00:01:47.980
Please find the exact connector ports of each models.

00:01:53.700 --> 00:01:58.800
Once the installation is completed, you will see the LOGIN page on the screen. 

00:01:59.200 --> 00:02:02.600
Now, you can enter the default username and password.

00:02:02.680 --> 00:02:08.000
The default username is “webadmin” and the password is “admin”

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:12.700
Then select your preferred UI language and click Login.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:17.300
Now we can see the main page of the SMP-NEO web manager

00:02:17.300 --> 00:02:20.900
Let’s take a quick overview of the user interface

00:02:20.900 --> 00:02:26.100
As we can see, SMP-NEO web manager has two-level menus.

00:02:26.100 --> 00:02:31.400
Click an item in the main menu and you will see more selections in the sub-menu.

00:02:31.400 --> 00:02:38.500
In the upper-right corner you can change the”System Time” and also manage your account in “Account and Shortcut”

00:02:38.500 --> 00:02:48.500
If you have questions about any specific function, you can simply go to the configuration page of the function and click HELP on top of the window. 

00:02:48.500 --> 00:02:54.600
If you want to change the language settings, go to the “Language” at the bottom of the page.

00:02:54.700 --> 00:03:03.200
For detailed instructions of a specific function, please check out other tutorial videos or go to the online help on each page.

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:08.200
Thank you for watching and thank you for choosing CAYIN Technology.

